            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Understanding HOA Architectural Review Processes: Most Green Valley master-planned retirement communities require architectural review committee (ARC) approval before solar installation. While Arizona Solar Rights Laws (ARS §33-1816 and §33-439) protect homeowners' rights to install solar, HOAs retain authority over aesthetic considerations including panel placement, equipment visibility, and color matching. Quail Creek Solar Requirements: ARC approval typically requires professional renderings showing panel placement, use of black-framed panels matching roof color (no visible silver frames), inverter and conduit concealment from street view, adherence to 3-foot fire setback requirements, and submission of complete installation plans. Our Quail Creek approval rate is 100% thanks to experience with specific ARC preferences and established relationships with board members. San Ignacio Golf Club Requirements: Similar to Quail Creek with additional emphasis on maintaining golf course viewsheds, screening equipment from fairway views, and using low-profile racking systems. Continental Reserve & Desert Hills Requirements: Focus on maintaining community aesthetics, color-matched equipment, and professional installation quality. We manage all submissions including professional CAD drawings, 3D renderings showing installed appearance, equipment specifications and color documentation, structural engineering certifications, and fire code compliance documentation."
