            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Why Tile Roofs Require Specialized Solar Expertise: Over 70% of Green Valley homes feature Spanish clay or concrete tile roofs creating unique installation challenges requiring specialized training and experience. Tile Roof Challenges: Tiles are fragile and easily crack during removal/replacement (broken tiles cost $8-$15 each), tile profiles vary widely (Spanish S-tile, flat concrete, barrel tile, interlocking patterns) requiring different techniques, under-tile waterproofing is critical (tiles alone aren't waterproof—underlayment provides protection), structural attachments must reach roof trusses beneath tiles and underlayment, and improper installation can void roof warranties or create leak paths. Why Many Solar Companies Avoid Tile Roofs: National solar companies often lack tile roof expertise (most installers trained on composition shingles), tile installations take 30-50% longer than shingle roofs, tile breakage risk creates liability concerns, and additional specialized labor increases costs. This means many solar companies either decline tile roof jobs or subcontract to local installers—adding costs and reducing quality control."
