            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Pre-Installation Preparations for Smooth Solar Installation: While we handle virtually all installation requirements, a few simple preparations ensure the smoothest possible solar installation experience for Green Valley homeowners. Roof & Attic Access: Ensure clear pathways to attic access points (installers need attic access for conduit runs), remove stored items blocking attic hatches, verify garage door openers work properly (equipment staged in garages), and trim vegetation blocking roof access if safety concerns exist. Electrical Panel Access: Clear area around electrical panel (3-foot clearance required by code), remove stored items from garage or utility room where panels located, ensure panel room is accessible, and notify us of any panel access challenges during consultation. Driveway & Equipment Staging: Reserve driveway space for installation day (crew arrives with equipment truck and ladder rack), plan alternative parking for homeowner vehicles, keep garage bay available if possible for equipment staging and weather protection, and ensure no scheduled deliveries or services conflict with installation day."
